{"title":"PNW Loam Carbon Handlebar Offers Predictable Comfort with CBD Layup","link":"https://bikerumor.com/pnw-loam-carbon-handlebar-review/","date":1698694771000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2500\" height=\"1667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-13.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-13.jpg 2500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-13-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-13-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-13-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-13-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-13-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-13-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-13-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>If your hands are telling you it’s time for a new handlebar, PNW Components have a new item on the menu. Their new Loam Carbon handlebar is their top shelf offering, though it’s made to be comfortable and predictable more than anything else. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Screenshot-2023-10-30-at-3.37.29 PM.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1902\" height=\"1984\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Screenshot-2023-10-30-at-3.37.29 PM.png\" alt=\"PNW loam bar testing chart\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Screenshot-2023-10-30-at-3.37.29 PM.png 1902w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Screenshot-2023-10-30-at-3.37.29 PM-288x300.png 288w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Screenshot-2023-10-30-at-3.37.29 PM-800x834.png 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Screenshot-2023-10-30-at-3.37.29 PM-115x120.png 115w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Screenshot-2023-10-30-at-3.37.29 PM-768x801.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Screenshot-2023-10-30-at-3.37.29 PM-1473x1536.png 1473w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There are plenty of handlebars on the market, so how do you choose the right one? For PNW, that involved a process of in-house and third-party testing of horizontal &amp; vertical deflection. According to PNW, the horizontal deflection is what’s responsible for a bar feeling predictable or unpredictable. The vertical deflection results in a bar feeling comfortable or stiff. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The intersection of the two is what PNW was after, with the goal of a comfortable &amp; predictable bar. They claim to have accomplished this with CBD. No, not the questionable supplement, but their Compliant Bore Design. Using EPS molding, PNW was able to create a unique inner bore profile that has a consistent, optimized wall thickness. Essentially, they are able to control the design of the inside of the handlebar as well as the outside. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>When produced with pre-preg UD carbon fiber, PNW claims to have found the perfect middle-ground for carbon handlebars. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>PNW Loam Bar Specs</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-loam-carbon-handlebar-specs2.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1760\" height=\"1043\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-loam-carbon-handlebar-specs2.png\" alt=\"PNW Loam Carbon handlebar specs\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-loam-carbon-handlebar-specs2.png 1760w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-loam-carbon-handlebar-specs2-297x176.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-loam-carbon-handlebar-specs2-800x474.png 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-loam-carbon-handlebar-specs2-120x71.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-loam-carbon-handlebar-specs2-768x455.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-loam-carbon-handlebar-specs2-1536x910.png 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to the bar itself, the PNW Loam Bar is currently offered only in 800mm widths with a 35mm clamp (31.8mm bars are in development). You can choose between a 25mm or 38mm rise, both with 5º upsweep, and 10º backsweep. That geometry is the same found on their Range Gen 3 handlebar for a slightly more upright riding position. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Loam bar is available in a matte black finish with satin PNW branding, and additional color decal sets are offered for $5 each. The PNW Loam Carbon bar is priced at $145. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Actual Weight</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-01.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-01-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"pnw grips actual weight\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-01-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-01-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-01-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-01-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-01-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-01-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-01-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-03.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-03-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"pnw stem actual weight\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-03-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-03-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-03-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-03-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-03-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-03-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-03-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-02.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-02-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"pnw stem actual weight\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-02-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-02-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-02-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-02-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-02-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-02-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-02-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-04.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-04-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"PNW Loam carbon bar review actual weight\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-04-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-04-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-04-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-04-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-04-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-04-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-Carbon-handlebar-review-04-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For an 800mm wide bar, the PNW Loam bar is decently light at 229g. And since PNW sent out a cockpit kit, we also weighed the grips (96g), and the Range Gen 3 stem. The stem sent was a 40mm length with 35mm clamp, which weighed in at 144g without the faceplate light/camera mount. The mount adds another 16g. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>First Impressions</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review1-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review1-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"PNW Loam carbon bar review\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review1-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review1-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review1-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review1-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review1-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review1-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review8-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review8-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"PNW Loam carbon bar review\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review8-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review8-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review8-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review8-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review8-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review8-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review4-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review4-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"PNW Loam carbon bar review\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review4-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review4-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review4-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review4-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review4-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review4-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review10-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review10-scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"PNW Loam carbon bar review\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review10-scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review10-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review10-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review10-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review10-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review10-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/PNW-Loam-bar-review10-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When it came time for testing, our REI Co-Op DRT e3.1 test bike seemed like a worthy platform. The bike comes stock with a Promax aluminum bar &amp; stem setup, and I’ve been putting a lot of miles on it over the peak of fall riding season. The ride comfort is noticeably better compared to the aluminum bar, with my hands feeling much more fresh at the end of a 29 mile ride. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Is it better than other carbon handlebars? That question will require more back-to-back testing, but rest assured the Loam Carbon bar is worth the price of admission. The quality is excellent, the geometry is dialed, and visually it looks like an upgrade as well. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.pnwcomponents.com/pages/the-loam-carbon-handlebar\"><em>pnwcomponents.com</em></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/pnw-loam-carbon-handlebar-review/\">PNW Loam Carbon Handlebar Offers Predictable Comfort with CBD Layup</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"13fada7ff51bda601f3892512aa66af4fd1c56c59fb902901bf6ad326a854122","category":"Cycling"}